Welcome to Fantasy Island!

266
00:28:57,919 --> 00:28:58,802
Croft.

267
00:29:00,020 --> 00:29:01,177
Hello, Terry.

268
00:29:09,830 --> 00:29:11,523
So what do you think of my new place?

269
00:29:12,884 --> 00:29:14,548
Not quite Croft manner.

270
00:29:16,872 --> 00:29:18,424
What, a key to your heart?

271
00:29:19,253 --> 00:29:21,096
To a flat in Zurich.

272
00:29:23,708 --> 00:29:25,671
You can pick another city if you want.

273
00:29:25,576 --> 00:29:28,267
Your record will be expound, your citizenship restored.

274
00:29:28,268 --> 00:29:28,924
Why?

275
00:29:29,306 --> 00:29:30,397
MI-6.

276
00:29:30,398 --> 00:29:31,557
MI-6.

277
00:29:32,503 --> 00:29:33,834
Now, without meet me first with devil?

278
00:29:36,199 --> 00:29:37,260
Well, you can pick one.

279
00:29:37,261 --> 00:29:39,361
because MI-6 would also arrange a new identity

280
00:29:39,563 --> 00:29:41,688
Oh yeah, do you think I need their help?

281
00:29:42,089 --> 00:29:44,353
Oh, having two faces doesn't count.

282
00:29:46,114 --> 00:29:48,166
So what do I have to do?

283
00:29:48,989 --> 00:29:50,825
You need to take me to the Shay Ling.

284
00:29:50,826 --> 00:29:51,710
She who?

285
00:29:52,446 --> 00:29:53,892
There's a man named Chen Lo

286
00:29:53,937 --> 00:29:56,352
who took something from me and
I want it back.

287
00:29:56,353 --> 00:29:58,739
Yeah. Is that you, or MI-6?

288
00:29:58,739 --> 00:30:00,468
Also, I've arranged the government

289
00:30:00,469 --> 00:30:02,837
to wire you 5 million in sterling
when we succeed.

290
00:30:02,837 --> 00:30:04,724
you can call it second chance, man.

291
00:30:04,725 --> 00:30:06,026
All right, then insurance for you?

292
00:30:07,035 --> 00:30:08,101
I don't need any.

293
00:30:12,528 --> 00:30:14,609
You and I working alone?

294
00:30:14,610 --> 00:30:17,254
And it's easier to see through you, that way.

295
00:30:18,592 --> 00:30:20,582
So what if afterwards

296
00:30:20,583 --> 00:30:24,820
MI-6 decide that me back in the world
isn't such a great idea?

297
00:30:24,821 --> 00:30:29,150
Then I'll feel sorry for whomever
they get to come after you.

298
00:30:33,452 --> 00:30:36,145
Do you have authorization to kill me, Croft?

299
00:30:36,102 --> 00:30:38,251
Any time, for any reason.

300
00:30:38,165 --> 00:30:40,436
So why don't you just do it now?

301
00:30:40,437 --> 00:30:43,070
What is it they see?

302
00:30:43,071 --> 00:30:45,413
Hell have no fury.

303
00:30:45,414 --> 00:30:46,446
You're not that good.

304
00:30:47,251 --> 00:30:49,742
Shay Ling and the groove's Croft.

305
00:30:51,546 --> 00:30:52,993
They move constantly.

306
00:30:53,390 --> 00:30:56,691
And they're in almost the most
remote mountain region in China.

307
00:30:57,104 --> 00:30:58,391
Region?

308
00:30:59,243 --> 00:31:00,892
You have to do better than that.

309
00:31:13,722 --> 00:31:17,892
Get me into China, and I'll get you to them in a day.

310
00:31:17,893 --> 00:31:22,236
No guns, no women, no weapons, when you come.

311
00:31:41,743 --> 00:31:43,796
Shay Ling has spies all over China.

312
00:31:43,797 --> 00:31:45,770
We have to get into country undetected

313
00:31:45,571 --> 00:31:48,142
so we'll slip into Beijing, and we go by truck.

314
00:31:48,142 --> 00:31:48,879
Truck?

315
00:31:48,879 --> 00:31:52,369
I wasn't thinking about
something a little faster.

316
00:31:58,849 --> 00:32:00,538
A little faster?

317
00:32:03,641 --> 00:32:07,313
Well, this is a little faster.
But the Chinese will pick the part.

318
00:32:10,159 --> 00:32:11,627
There won't be any part to find.

319
00:32:11,646 --> 00:32:13,306
Will there be any of us to fight?

320
00:32:21,018 --> 00:32:23,245
-Ready? now!
-Ready for what?

321
00:32:42,541 --> 00:32:45,691
What you did was good, Croft.
I'll give you that.

322
00:32:46,871 --> 00:32:49,930
But we're never going to feign
the equal of a place like this

323
00:32:55,019 --> 00:32:55,933
ni3 hao3

324
00:32:55,934 --> 00:32:56,619
ni3 hao3

325
00:32:57,787 --> 00:32:59,261
It's lovely to see you

326
00:33:02,585 --> 00:33:04,129
So is everything ready?

327
00:33:04,130 --> 00:33:08,295
Yes. Your clothes, guns, and knives, are over there.

328
00:33:09,645 --> 00:33:12,832
And I took the liberty of tuning your bike.

329
00:33:13,133 --> 00:33:14,747
-May I?
-Yes.

330
00:33:32,387 --> 00:33:33,676
Lara.

331
00:33:33,677 --> 00:33:36,175
Ah, what is the happy couple up to?

332
00:33:36,208 --> 00:33:37,814
Accessorizing.

333
00:33:38,315 --> 00:33:40,504
Where are we all on reading the orb?

334
00:33:40,505 --> 00:33:43,328
All maps have a key, Lara, scale or legend, yes?

335
00:33:43,529 --> 00:33:45,364
The orb's key is not on orbit,

336
00:33:45,264 --> 00:33:46,426
it must have been lost.

337
00:33:46,698 --> 00:33:48,637
or somewhere in the temple

338
00:33:48,938 --> 00:33:50,859
Go through every image I took

339
00:33:50,859 --> 00:33:52,294
start with the ones near the orb.

340
00:33:53,304 --> 00:33:55,419
key must have been linked to it in some way.

341
00:33:55,591 --> 00:33:58,445
Right, well then...

342
00:33:58,446 --> 00:34:01,304
It's unlike Lara to take a partner.

343
00:34:01,305 --> 00:34:03,251
Where are you two going?

344
00:34:03,452 --> 00:34:05,742
We're taking a nice little trip.

345
00:34:05,743 --> 00:34:07,893
breathe some fresh mountain air

346
00:34:09,493 --> 00:34:11,792
stop by my friends the Shay Ling

347
00:34:24,876 --> 00:34:27,131
Shay Ling watch all the roads.

348
00:34:27,227 --> 00:34:28,782
We have to go around the back.

349
00:34:28,782 --> 00:34:30,337
We'll go straight.

350
00:34:31,252 --> 00:34:32,252
Maybe you didn't hear me

351
00:34:32,854 --> 00:34:35,857
Shay Ling have men on every road
from here to Luo Yang.

352
00:34:37,425 --> 00:34:38,314
Not every road.

353
00:35:12,251 --> 00:35:13,996
Getting rusty, are we?

354
00:35:13,997 --> 00:35:15,288
Oh, I think it's coming back.

355
00:35:15,988 --> 00:35:18,187
I expect the move is gone.

356
00:35:18,187 --> 00:35:20,969
I don't expect anything from an English woman.

357
00:35:21,809 --> 00:35:23,661
Good, cause you're not going to get anything.

358
00:36:03,574 --> 00:36:04,696
Party's over.

359
00:36:05,190 --> 00:36:07,154
From now on it's by foot.

360
00:36:10,447 --> 00:36:13,018
I see you can reconsider that no gun rule.

361
00:36:13,419 --> 00:36:14,076
No.

362
00:36:25,786 --> 00:36:27,533
And don't be looking at my ass.

363
00:36:29,784 --> 00:36:31,194
So where do I fit in?

364
00:36:31,195 --> 00:36:32,281
What do you mean?

365
00:36:32,282 --> 00:36:33,010
You'll the guide.

366
00:36:33,011 --> 00:36:35,378
I mean...when you think back

367
00:36:35,379 --> 00:36:38,468
on the vast scheme of hugely adventurous life

368
00:36:38,770 --> 00:36:40,681
where do I fit in?

369
00:36:41,331 --> 00:36:42,595
Is that a love of your life?

370
00:36:42,596 --> 00:36:44,684
Or just another bump on the road?

371
00:36:45,185 --> 00:36:47,285
Was that time well spent?

372
00:36:47,227 --> 00:36:48,828
Four months, whether good or bad.

373
00:36:51,630 --> 00:36:54,170
Come on I had to be more than that, am I right?

374
00:36:56,452 --> 00:36:57,367
All right.

375
00:36:58,794 --> 00:37:00,341
It was five months.

376
00:37:03,181 --> 00:37:04,471
You're not laughing at me?

377
00:37:04,645 --> 00:37:06,897
No. It's the fact that I used to find you charming.

378
00:37:09,473 --> 00:37:10,940
I am charming.

379
00:37:38,123 --> 00:37:38,951
You're late.

380
00:37:44,707 --> 00:37:47,628
The bank, do it.

381
00:37:51,903 --> 00:37:54,798
You won't see again in a hour, maybe.

382
00:38:06,365 --> 00:38:07,208
What's this?

383
00:38:08,194 --> 00:38:09,284
It's not there.

384
00:38:10,072 --> 00:38:11,267
There's no orb.

385
00:38:13,315 --> 00:38:15,237
Is it anything you can tell me about this?

386
00:38:31,738 --> 00:38:32,460
Hello.

387
00:38:32,678 --> 00:38:34,853
I take it you don't like your messenger

388
00:38:34,854 --> 00:38:38,374
I didn't, but I did like the men lost in a temple.

389
00:38:38,668 --> 00:38:40,977
You underestimated Lady Croft.

390
00:38:41,204 --> 00:38:45,478
I underestimated how much this orb is worth.

391
00:38:45,522 --> 00:38:48,367
So many horrible diseases in the world

392
00:38:48,368 --> 00:38:51,930
things that are particularly susceptible to our children

393
00:38:51,931 --> 00:38:54,504
You'll never know when you'll be holding a little sheal or

394
00:38:54,505 --> 00:38:59,366
or tie by the hand with the mysterious illness in their bodies

395
00:39:00,034 --> 00:39:01,012
If you kill them,

396
00:39:01,666 --> 00:39:04,429
and I'll give your orb to Lady Croft.

397
00:39:04,557 --> 00:39:08,364
My men tell me, she's a few miles away from here
as we speak.

398
00:39:08,931 --> 00:39:10,740
I wonder how much she would pay

399
00:39:11,125 --> 00:39:14,202
I'll pay you an additional $12 million dollars.

400
00:39:14,203 --> 00:39:17,233
It will be yours when she has delivered the orb to me

401
00:39:17,234 --> 00:39:19,702
along with Lady Croft's body.

402
00:39:19,928 --> 00:39:22,249
I don't think you know where they are.

403
00:39:22,250 --> 00:39:23,251
You're impossible you know that.

404
00:39:23,252 --> 00:39:26,898
I think you pretended to know
so I would get you out.

405
00:39:26,899 --> 00:39:31,026
This isn't a tomb Croft,
and Shay Ling aren't mummies.

406
00:39:31,227 --> 00:39:32,494
They're killers.

407
00:39:32,495 --> 00:39:34,580
But if you don't trust me,

408
00:39:39,841 --> 00:39:42,293
I'm sorry I have to do this
but you're wasting time.

409
00:39:47,150 --> 00:39:48,639
You want to shoot me, shoot me.

410
00:39:49,734 --> 00:39:54,027
Personally, I'd rather you do it than them.

411
00:40:00,235 --> 00:40:06,635
bu xu dong (Stay right there!)

412
00:40:12,920 --> 00:40:16,507
Well, Terry, what part of "never come back again"

413
00:40:16,908 --> 00:40:18,478
didn't you understand?

414
00:40:22,402 --> 00:40:24,080
You wanted to fight the Shay Ling.

415
00:40:28,103 --> 00:40:31,497
The only way to get into their place
is as their prisoners.

416
00:40:31,498 --> 00:40:34,142
You want to tell me that in jail before.

417
00:40:34,143 --> 00:40:35,003
Would you have believed me?

418
00:40:35,275 --> 00:40:38,780
Make Chen Lo a better offer than his buyer

419
00:40:38,781 --> 00:40:39,820
you cross them.

420
00:40:40,220 --> 00:40:42,313
Even if his buyer is Jonathan Reiss.

421
00:40:43,837 --> 00:40:46,055
You may have told me that lot in gem before.

422
00:41:30,469 --> 00:41:32,083
Were you really going to kill me?

423
00:41:32,473 --> 00:41:33,996
Oh, I bet you would have

424
00:41:35,543 --> 00:41:36,795
I've seen her in action.

425
00:41:37,708 --> 00:41:38,729
Didn't Terry tell you?

426
00:41:39,123 --> 00:41:41,421
The last time any of us saw him,

427
00:41:41,772 --> 00:41:43,987
he was riding away with a truck

428
00:41:44,301 --> 00:41:46,202
full of my many vases

429
00:41:47,646 --> 00:41:53,034
and sitting next to him, was his sister

430
00:41:55,437 --> 00:41:56,337
Oh, how is she?

431
00:41:56,338 --> 00:41:57,502
You

432
00:41:57,904 --> 00:42:00,070
shouldn't come here

433
00:42:01,797 --> 00:42:02,850
They got me out of prison

434
00:42:03,440 --> 00:42:05,417
this here lady has a good offer

435
00:42:06,184 --> 00:42:07,452
better than Reiss.

436
00:42:07,932 --> 00:42:09,159
Really?

437
00:42:09,159 --> 00:42:10,786
Should I take it?

438
00:42:11,558 --> 00:42:12,384
Take it.

439
00:42:12,385 --> 00:42:14,366
Or better yet,

440
00:42:14,366 --> 00:42:17,593
you and I run some horrendous thing
back to the British for triple.

441
00:42:20,064 --> 00:42:21,016
Let's talk.

442
00:42:22,051 --> 00:42:23,249
Not you, Terry.

443
00:42:24,730 --> 00:42:26,746
Lady Croft and I.

444
00:42:27,047 --> 00:42:28,145
You wait here.

445
00:42:29,725 --> 00:42:30,769
Catch up.

446
00:42:30,770 --> 00:42:33,001
There will be four minute.

447
00:42:34,705 --> 00:42:36,093
Terrific!

448
00:42:39,979 --> 00:42:41,947
There's something I think you will have appreciated

449
00:42:52,127 --> 00:42:55,924
This is the largest terracotta warriors I've found.

450
00:42:57,087 --> 00:42:59,007
The king of Qin made them

451
00:42:59,200 --> 00:43:00,924
for use in the afterlife

452
00:43:00,996 --> 00:43:04,927
to fend off enemies he may

453
00:43:04,928 --> 00:43:07,243
Sounds like we could both use it there.

454
00:43:09,123 --> 00:43:11,049
I'd be happy to sell some to you.

455
00:43:12,101 --> 00:43:14,306
I hope you're as entrepreneurial with the Orb.

456
00:43:14,559 --> 00:43:17,116
You've lost men, I've lost men

457
00:43:18,216 --> 00:43:20,470
I see no reason we should both lose again.

458
00:43:20,471 --> 00:43:23,874
If I want double, would Reiss offer it to me?

459
00:43:23,875 --> 00:43:24,331
Is it here?

460
00:43:25,007 --> 00:43:26,266
It's worth a lot.

461
00:43:26,267 --> 00:43:27,926
Well then, if you know that,

462
00:43:27,926 --> 00:43:30,633
you'll know Reiss will also kill you
the moment you give them to him.

463
00:43:31,354 --> 00:43:33,409
And your government would guarantee my safety?

464
00:43:33,486 --> 00:43:34,560
No.

465
00:43:34,888 --> 00:43:35,930
But I will.

466
00:43:36,432 --> 00:43:40,373
That must hurt, saying that to me.

467
00:43:41,564 --> 00:43:42,695
Take the offer.

468
00:43:51,749 --> 00:43:53,438
You presume to give me orders?

469
00:43:53,836 --> 00:43:56,422
Take the offer before it expires.

470
00:43:56,423 --> 00:43:58,308
No.

471
00:43:58,510 --> 00:44:00,427
Then I would have to force you.

472
00:44:00,528 --> 00:44:01,858
Then I would have to kill you.

473
00:45:13,894 --> 00:45:15,156
Has it been four minutes yet?

474
00:45:59,936 --> 00:46:01,288
Loverboy,

475
00:46:03,141 --> 00:46:05,273
It's too bad, you're on the wrong side

476
00:46:07,915 --> 00:46:10,974
Tell me where the orb is,
and I'll spare your life.

477
00:46:14,481 --> 00:46:17,194
The Flower Pagoda in Shanghai, 9 PM.

478
00:46:21,476 --> 00:46:22,743
This is mine.

479
00:46:33,050 --> 00:46:34,572
Now, we're even.

480
00:46:43,318 --> 00:46:44,985
Freeze! Put your hands up!

481
00:47:08,599 --> 00:47:10,771
Remember that no gun rule? I reconsidered.

482
00:47:43,562 --> 00:47:46,214
Lara, there was a staircase we could have used.

483
00:48:13,405 --> 00:48:14,669
Lorie, are you all right?

484
00:48:15,056 --> 00:48:17,984
rushing, I'm on my way to Shanghai

485
00:48:18,107 --> 00:48:19,722
And I need you to look at something for me.

486
00:48:21,466 --> 00:48:23,367
It's in the Luna Temple near the orb.

487
00:48:24,208 --> 00:48:26,220
And I'm betting it's key to those markings.

488
00:48:27,762 --> 00:48:30,471
She's holding some sort of musical instrument.

489
00:48:32,583 --> 00:48:33,846
It's sound.

490
00:48:35,048 --> 00:48:36,017
That's brilliant.

491
00:48:36,124 --> 00:48:38,690
Key must have linked into it some way

492
00:48:38,691 --> 00:48:40,605
I'll start decoding the images we have.

493
00:48:40,605 --> 00:48:42,585
-Good.
-You give us the rest, bye, Lara.

494
00:48:42,707 --> 00:48:43,255
-Miss you.
-Bye.

495
00:48:46,533 --> 00:48:50,876
[Shanghai]

496
00:49:01,113 --> 00:49:04,162
Flower Pagoda, 8:50 pm

497
00:49:39,167 --> 00:49:42,370
Trouble is coming, let's go.

498
00:49:51,083 --> 00:49:55,551
well.

499
00:49:56,282 --> 00:49:57,382
Just like old times.

500
00:50:02,495 --> 00:50:07,424
I think that's the first time you've
actually smelt because of me

501
00:50:14,599 --> 00:50:15,923
Why did you do it?

502
00:50:16,653 --> 00:50:18,240
I started thinking.

503
00:50:18,241 --> 00:50:21,861
I was...tired of doing things for somebody else's way

504
00:50:21,862 --> 00:50:24,393
and it was always going to be somebody else's way.

505
00:50:24,494 --> 00:50:27,037
So you abandoned your men and
betrayed your country.

506
00:50:28,546 --> 00:50:30,467
Leaving my men and my country

507
00:50:30,468 --> 00:50:33,090
that didn't actually hurt as much as I thought.

508
00:50:34,472 --> 00:50:36,307
Believe me you would do it.

509
00:50:39,690 --> 00:50:41,824
that hard to follow Croft.

510
00:50:47,365 --> 00:50:50,600
Do you know why you and I got
along for a while?

511
00:50:51,335 --> 00:50:51,885
No.

512
00:50:53,872 --> 00:50:56,539
We are two of a kind, me and you.

513
00:51:00,247 --> 00:51:01,908
We are nothing alike.

514
00:51:01,699 --> 00:51:03,343
-I don't think we're alike.
-Um hm.

515
00:51:04,915 --> 00:51:06,502
But do you think we're a pair?

516
00:51:06,541 --> 00:51:09,466
say it's the same coin.

517
00:51:34,819 --> 00:51:36,882
My men have the roof covered.

518
00:51:36,883 --> 00:51:38,969
Why don't you set down at the square instead.

519
00:51:39,110 --> 00:51:42,373
That way, my men would also have things covered.

520
00:51:42,488 --> 00:51:44,123
Okay, fine.

521
00:51:44,528 --> 00:51:46,357
Okay, so, let's go!

522
00:51:50,888 --> 00:51:52,779
We're arriving at the square.

523
00:51:54,698 --> 00:51:55,973
We're in the wrong position.

524
00:51:56,330 --> 00:51:57,701
-Steels? -No time.

525
00:51:57,833 --> 00:51:59,012
-Wet tapes?
-No.

526
00:51:59,466 --> 00:52:00,547
I've got a plan!

527
00:52:01,181 --> 00:52:03,512
Stay here, wait for my signal.

528
00:52:07,953 --> 00:52:10,308
Here's your money, come and get it.

529
00:52:18,857 --> 00:52:20,405
Wait for my signal, pal.

530
00:52:20,706 --> 00:52:21,699
Give me that box!

531
00:52:21,700 --> 00:52:22,712
